ray, AP portable chest X-ray, Expiratory PA chest\nX-ray\n• Chest CT\n• Chest MRI\n• PET scanning\nChest X-ray\n• The most commonly ordered X-ray is a chest X-ray, which is the quickest and most\ncost-effective way to begin imaging the thorax.\n• PA and lateral chest X-ray gives valuable information and serves as a baseline to\nconfirm the effectiveness of treatment.\n• An AP chest is done when the patient is unable to be moved, usually because of\nthe illness severity.\nPA: stands for posterior to anterior. As the patient stands with the anterior chest wall\nclosest to the film. X-rays pass from posterior to anterior to expose the film.\nIn this position, the heart is closer to the film than on an AP view and there is less\nmagnification of the cardiac silhouette.\n62"}